The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Sports | Chetri may play against United
                                                                                                                       7                                        Chetri may play against United
            OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT            Sunil Chetri                           
	New Delhi: India striker Sunil Chetri would be seen in action against top stars like Paul Scholes, Ryan Giggs, Nani and Dimitar Berbatov when the Kansas City Wizards take on Manchester United in a friendly tie at the New Arrowhead Stadium, in Kansas City, on Sunday.         
	According to Kansas City coach Peter Vermes, the diminutive Indian forward, who joined the MLS side early this season, has a bright chance of being in the starting line-up against the star-studded Premier League side.         
	We are looking forward to Sunil getting the opportunity to play, Vermes said. He has been working very hard and this game will give him a chance to measure himself against some of the best players in the world.         
	Chetri scored in his debut game as a substitute in an exhibition tie against the University of Tulsa and followed it up with a hattrick against the University of Evansville in another reserves game in April.         
	Im very excited, Chetri said. Its an once-in-a-lifetime opportunity to play against the best team in the world.         
	Chetri was one of 30 players recently selected for the Indian national teams ongoing preparations for the 2011 Asian Cup, but chief coach Bob Houghton indicated Chetri would join the team towards the end of the year.                                                                                                                     
